The official GitHub MCP server allows AI agents and tools to interact with GitHub’s platform, enabling capabilities like reading repositories, managing issues and pull requests, and automating workflows through natural language [1][2]. GitHub provides both a remote server, which is the easiest to use and requires no local setup, and a local version for specific hosting needs [1][3].

To configure the remote server in compatible editors like VS Code, add the following to your host configuration:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "github": {
      "type": "http",
      "url": "https://api.githubcopilot.com/mcp/"
    }
  }
}
```

The remote server requires an access token, such as a GitHub Personal Access Token or an OAuth token, provided via the Authorization header [1][3]. Always refer to the [official GitHub MCP repository](https://github.com/github/github-mcp-server) for the latest installation guidance and toolset configurations [2].
